LaunchDock Installation Instructions
====================================

MACOS INSTALLATION
==================

1. INSTALL THE APPLICATION
---------------------------

1. Open the downloaded DMG file
2. Drag LaunchDock.app to your Applications folder
3. Eject the DMG

2. FIRST LAUNCH
---------------

On first launch, macOS will show a security warning because the app is not signed:

1. Right-click on LaunchDock.app in Applications
2. Select "Open"
3. Click "Open" in the dialog

This only needs to be done once.

3. ADD COMMAND LINE ACCESS (OPTIONAL)
-------------------------------------

To use launchdock commands from Terminal:

    sudo ln -sf /Applications/LaunchDock.app/Contents/MacOS/launchdock /usr/local/bin/launchdock

Verify installation:

    launchdock status

4. SET UP KEYBOARD SHORTCUT
---------------------------

METHOD 1: Shortcuts App (macOS Monterey 12.0+, Recommended)

1. Open Shortcuts app (Spotlight: search "Shortcuts")
2. Click + button (top right) to create new shortcut
3. Search for and add action: "Open App"
4. Click "App" and select LaunchDock
5. Name your shortcut: "Launch LaunchDock" (top of editor)
6. Right-click your new shortcut → "Shortcut Details" (or click ⓘ icon)
7. Click "Add Keyboard Shortcut"
8. Press your desired key combo (e.g., ⌘Space, ⌥Space)
9. Click Done

If the shortcut doesn't work, grant permissions:
System Settings → Privacy & Security → Accessibility → Enable Shortcuts

METHOD 2: Automator (Alternative)

1. Open Automator → New Document → Quick Action
2. Set Workflow receives: "no input" in "any application"
3. Add action: Launch Application
4. Select LaunchDock.app
5. Save as: "Launch LaunchDock"
6. System Settings → Keyboard → Keyboard Shortcuts → Services
7. Find "Launch LaunchDock" and assign your hotkey

Recommended hotkey combinations:
- ⌘Space (Command + Space)
- ⌥Space (Option + Space)
- ^Space (Control + Space)

5. ENABLE AUTO-START AT LOGIN (OPTIONAL)
-----------------------------------------

To start LaunchDock automatically when you log in:

1. System Settings → General → Login Items
2. Click + button under "Open at Login"
3. Navigate to Applications and select LaunchDock.app
4. Click Add

6. COMMAND LINE OPTIONS
-----------------------

Once symlinked, you can use:

    launchdock status    # Check daemon status
    launchdock logs      # View logs
    launchdock stop      # Stop daemon
    launchdock start     # Start daemon
    launchdock show      # Show UI

7. UNINSTALL
------------

Remove symlink:
    sudo rm /usr/local/bin/launchdock

Remove app:
    rm -rf /Applications/LaunchDock.app


WINDOWS INSTALLATION
====================

1. EXTRACT AND INSTALL BINARY
------------------------------

Extract the downloaded archive and copy launchdock.exe to a directory in your PATH.

Common installation locations:
- C:\Program Files\LaunchDock\
- C:\Users\YourName\AppData\Local\Programs\LaunchDock\

2. ADD TO PATH
--------------

1. Search for "Environment Variables" in Windows Search
2. Click "Edit the system environment variables"
3. Click "Environment Variables"
4. Under "User variables", select "Path" and click "Edit"
5. Click "New" and add the directory containing launchdock.exe
6. Click OK on all dialogs

3. START THE DAEMON
-------------------

Open Command Prompt or PowerShell and run:

    launchdock start

4. CONFIGURE STARTUP (RECOMMENDED)
----------------------------------

To run automatically at startup:

METHOD 1: Task Scheduler

1. Open Task Scheduler
2. Create Basic Task
3. Name: LaunchDock
4. Trigger: When I log on
5. Action: Start a program
6. Program: C:\Path\To\launchdock.exe
7. Arguments: start
8. Finish

METHOD 2: Startup Folder

1. Press Win+R, type: shell:startup
2. Create shortcut to launchdock.exe
3. Right-click shortcut → Properties
4. In "Target", add " start" after the path

5. SET UP HOTKEYS
-----------------

Windows 11:
1. Settings → Accessibility → Keyboard
2. Enable "Use the Print Screen key to open screen capture"
   OR use third-party tools like AutoHotkey or PowerToys

PowerToys (Recommended):
1. Install PowerToys from Microsoft Store
2. Open PowerToys → Keyboard Manager → Remap a shortcut
3. Set shortcut to run: launchdock show

Suggested hotkey combinations:
- Ctrl+Alt+Space
- Win+Space


LINUX INSTALLATION
==================

1. EXTRACT AND INSTALL BINARY
------------------------------

Extract the downloaded archive and copy the launchdock binary to a directory in your PATH.

Common installation locations:
- /usr/local/bin/ (system-wide, requires sudo)
- ~/.local/bin/ (user-only)

Example:

    tar -xzf launchdock-linux.tar.gz
    sudo cp launchdock /usr/local/bin/
    sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/launchdock

2. START THE DAEMON
-------------------

Open a terminal and run:

    launchdock start

3. CONFIGURE STARTUP (RECOMMENDED)
----------------------------------

Add to your desktop environment's autostart:

GNOME:
1. Settings → Apps → Startup Applications
2. Click Add
3. Name: LaunchDock
4. Command: launchdock start
5. Click Add

KDE Plasma:
1. System Settings → Startup and Shutdown → Autostart
2. Click Add → Add Application
3. Select or type: launchdock start

Systemd (alternative):
Create ~/.config/systemd/user/launchdock.service:

    [Unit]
    Description=LaunchDock Daemon

    [Service]
    ExecStart=/usr/local/bin/launchdock start
    Restart=on-failure

    [Install]
    WantedBy=default.target

Enable:
    systemctl --user enable launchdock
    systemctl --user start launchdock

4. SET UP HOTKEYS
-----------------

GNOME:
1. Settings → Keyboard → Keyboard Shortcuts → Custom Shortcuts
2. Click + to add
3. Name: LaunchDock
4. Command: launchdock show
5. Set shortcut (e.g., Super+Space)

KDE Plasma:
1. System Settings → Shortcuts → Custom Shortcuts
2. Right-click → New → Global Shortcut → Command/URL
3. Trigger tab: Set your hotkey
4. Action tab: launchdock show

Suggested hotkey combinations:
- Super+Space (recommended)
- Ctrl+Alt+Space
- Meta+Escape


USAGE
=====

- Press your configured hotkey to show the launcher
- Type to search for applications (fuzzy matching supported)
- Use arrow keys or numbers (1-7) to select
- Press Enter to launch, Escape to close


TROUBLESHOOTING
===============

Daemon won't start:
    launchdock logs

Applications don't appear:
    launchdock stop && launchdock start

Check daemon status:
    launchdock status


For more help, visit:
https://github.com/qa3-tech/launchdock

